
[1]bankrupt-law

   BANK'RUPT-LAW, n. A law, which, upon a bankrupt's surrendering all his
   property to commissioners for the benefit of his creditors, discharges
   him from the payment of his debts,and all liability to arrest or suit
   for the same, and secures his future acquired property from a liability
   to the payment of his past debts.
